==English==
===Etymology===
[[Monday]] (start the work week) + [[-itis]] (affliction or disease); popularity of the term is purported to be traceable to its use in the 1999 American comedy film ''[[Wikipedia:Office Space|Office Space]]''
===Proper noun===
# the [[tired]] and [[apathetic]] feeling experienced by persons who work a regular work week upon the return to work after the [[weekend]]
===See also===
* Wikipedia article [[Wikipedia:Working time|Working time]], which places the term in context

